Order Online For Toggle navigation Menu Home FAQ Story Beer Cocktails Food Contact Us Store Our Story Drinking Problems Jackass Brewing Company started as a homebrewing hobby between founders Skip Kratzer and Larry At first they brewed every month or And then every few And finally every weekend had a day dedicated to But the more they brewed, the more they realized they both had a drinking problem – essentially that they made so much beer they couldn’t drink it So Skip and Larry started sharing their beer with friends, and that solved the problem in a In fact, they couldn’t keep up with The birth of a Jackass (or two) Shortly after they started making beer, the idea of opening a place in Lewisburg was In June of , Skip and Larry spent a week at the Portland Craft Beer Festival and visited over breweries in 5 It was pretty easy to see why some breweries were empty and others were Good beer was important, but they also realized that the brewery’s culture was what made good beer taste The partners broke ground in May of with a mission to bring good food, great beer and a love of community back to If it’s not a Jackass… One hot summer night at a pub in Williamspor

their families stay connected with their care It’s easy for a patient in hospice to feel isolated or alone, and Telehealth can allow a caretaker or family member to involve other loved ones through a , video call to include everyone in the hospice care process without having to be in the same room Massage Therapy Hospice massage is a natural treatment that can help patients find peace and Depending on the state of the patient, a massage treatment can vary from a full massage, to something for more fragile patients called attentive touch, which can ease discomfort wherever it is needed — such as a gentle foot massage or scalp massage, for Massage therapy can reduce stress and anxiety, as well as simply provide a healing presence through undivided attention met with a transformative response of calm and The physical benefits from touch include stabilized heart rate, lower blood pressure, endorphin release, a feeling of being cared for, and eased depression, fear and Pet Therapy Pets have a history of providing faithful companionship and showing unconditional love for This creates a powerful emotional bond that has a very positive Communication between humans and animals occurs on a deeper, more primitive level than the spoken Simply cuddling or petting an animal can reduce anxiety, lower blood pressure and heart rate, and ease Because a primary goal of hospice services is comfort care, Pet Therapy is an ideal option for providing comfort to patients who often feel Music Therapy The power of music is undeniable, especially for patients in A song from the past can bring life to a patient’s eyes that their families may have not seen in Music therapy can bind with other healing efforts to address the physical, emotional, cognitive, and social needs of hospice Remembrance Hand Molds Remembrance hand molds are a special keepsake that provide a permanent reminder of a loved This replica of a patient’s hand joined to another’s hand, is a loving tribute Acne is caused by dead skin cells and sebum (oil) that clog your hair follicles, leading to excess bacteria growth and In most people, a trigger like hormonal changes (think puberty or pregnancy! ) causes their sebaceous glands to overproduce Generally, sebum is considered a good thing because it protects your skin and hair, keeping them moisturized and Sebum also serves as a food source for Cutibacterium acnes (formerly Propionibacterium acnes ). This bacteria is thought to be responsible for preventing harmful bacteria from entering your pores [ 2 ]. “This acnes strain may protect the skin, much like yogurt’s live bacteria help defend the gut from harmful ” – Huiying Li, PhD However, excess sebum production leads to increased growth of acnes , which triggers an immune Your body sends white blood cells to neutralize this perceived threat, leading to inflammation and As a result, acnes is commonly referred to as bacteria, even though that’s only half the Does Red Light Therapy Help With Acne ? Yes, red light therapy can help with Unlike blue light, red light does not kill acnes But, it does penetrate deeper into the skin, targeting your sebaceous glands and reducing inflammation [ 3 ]. It can help reduce acne breakouts by soothing skin redness, normalizing sebum production, and reducing sebaceous gland In one study, researchers looked at RLT’s effects on both and inflammatory They saw, on average, a %+ They concluded that “red light phototherapy alone can be a new therapeutic option for acne vulgaris ” [ 4 ]. Best of all? What About Acne Scars ? Acne scarring occurs as a result of improper When acne becomes too clogged with excess oil, dead skin cells, and bacteria, it swells and ruptures, damaging your If this happens near your skin’s surface, it’ll usually heal quickly and leave little to no evidence But, if the acne penetrates deeper into your skin and ruptures, all the nasty stuff inside can spill out and damage more of your healthy skin Your skin enters “emergency-response mode” and builds new collagen fibers to repair the damage, but it can often produce too little or too This leads to Too little collagen leads to depressed acne scars (aka atrophic scars). Too much collagen leads to raised acne scars (aka hypertrophic scars). Because RLT has been shown to promote healing and normalize collagen production, it can help you prevent those pesky scars from ever What About Hyperpigmentation Acne ? Tornadoes are possible in and near the watch Review and discuss your emergency plans and check supplies and your safe ” Weather Service Watches are issued by the Storm Prediction Center and usually cover an area that can include multiple counties or a large When warm moist air closer to the ground and cooler dry air above come together, they can produce a supercell (rotating thunderstorm), which can often lead to Everyday, meteorologists analyze for these weather patterns and if those right ingredients come together, a watch could be issued a few hours prior to possible tornadic What does this mean for you? During the day, you should stay aware of the weather outside or any local weather stations who will keep you up to date on the current When a watch is issued, you should make sure you and anyone you may live with has a plan for what to do if the weather does get In an emergency situation, you want to make sure that you can take shelter immediately in a safe place with adequate Source: NWS – Example of a tornado watch issued for parts of Missouri, Arkansas, Oklahoma, and Kansas in Tornado warning “Take Action! A tornado has been sighted or indicated by weather There is imminent danger to life and ” Weather Service Warnings are issued by the National Weather Service and cover a much smaller area, such as a few small towns or sections of a When a radar indicates signs of a tornado directly touching down, a warning will be issued lasting a few minutes to The warning may end or be extended directly after this time Make sure to have the ability to connect with the news, emergency alerts, NOAA weather radio or hear the tornado siren from your local emergency management to understand if and when you will be under a When you know you are under a tornado warning, it is extremely important to take shelter immediately in a windowless, interior room or basement storm shelter and make sure you are covered with a blanket, mattress, pillows, and It is extremely important to make sure you put as many barriers between you and the outside weather as Blankets and helmets are valuable items during a tornado that can further protect you from any debris or falling objects and could potentially save your Source: NWS – Example of a tornado warning issued for Nashville, Tennessee and some other smaller Tornado Emergency This last category is relatively new and was introduced in for the Oklahoma City, OK F5 tornado that brought mass destruction and This is the highest alert that can be issued for a tornado event and is only used when there is certainty of devastating damage that can wipe out large portions of towns and During that tornado event, meteorologists issued a tornado warning but felt that it would not be enough to convey the magnitude of the On the spot, they came up with the concept of a tornado emergency When the F5 passed, there were fatalities, but there could have been many more if it were not for the National Weather Service coming up with new messaging to explain the catastrophic nature of some of these These emergencies do not come often in a year so when they do, it is extremely important that every single person is aware and taking In , the tornado emergency messaging was officially formalized after a particularly bad outbreak in Tennessee, Alabama, and Today, this messaging is reserved only if “severe threat to human life and catastrophic damage is imminent or ongoing and a reliable source confirms a destructive tornado visually or through radar,” the NWS Anxiety is an emotion that refers to concerns, worry, and or fear about a In clinical terms, anxiety refers to instances when a person experiences excessive fear or apprehension about a 1 “Fear is the emotional response to real or perceived imminent threat, whereas anxiety is anticipation of future ” 2 Anxiety, within normal bounds, can be a “ gift of wisdom .” 3 It acts as a tool, or indicator, to communicate our internal perceptions about the external It can prompt us to reflect on or prepare for stressful but important occasions, such as an exam, a first date, or a However, excessive anxiety can deeply affect our minds and bodies in negative Modern life—and its associated challenges—is conducive to abnormal levels of Our Western concepts of time management and our notion of productivity, the divisive rhetoric in the news media, and our , work environments contribute to heightened baseline “Anxiety… acts as a tool, or indicator, to communicate our internal perceptions about the external ” What Are the Symptoms of Anxiety? Symptoms of anxiety can vary among people, but some common ones are listed 4 , 5 , 6 Physical feelings of pressure on the chest pounding or racing heart shortness of breath sweating trembling or shaking muscle tension problems falling or staying asleep headaches, fatigue, or insomnia upset stomach, frequent urination, or diarrhea Emotional or Mental restlessness or irritability tension or jumpiness difficulty focusing or concentrating anticipating the worst and watching for signs of danger recurring intrusive thoughts irrational worries about objects or situations impending feelings of doom difficulty managing feelings of worry Types of Anxiety Disorders An anxiety disorder is a condition characterized by prolonged abnormal anxiety Anxiety disorders are the most prevalent mental health conditions in the In , an estimated million people experienced an anxiety disorder, 7 The World Health Organization estimates that anxiety disorders make up 4% of existing disabilities 8 Anxiety disorders comprise the following subgroupings, or types, according to the American Psychiatric Association’s Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders (5th edition ). 2 Specific Phobias People with specific phobias are excessively fearful of, are anxious about, or try to avoid certain objects or Anxiety is almost always immediately induced by an encounter with the feared object or It is usually both persistent and disproportionate to actual risk in the Various types of specific phobias include ones related to animals, the natural environment, blood, injections, and injury, but many others Social Anxiety Disorder In social anxiety disorder (also known as social phobia), a person is fearful of, is anxious about,

Each offers incrementally better breast cancer detection in dense breasts than mammography However, Eve Clear Scan™, using molecular breast imaging (MBI) technology, is superior to all of these An MBI examination employs an intravenous (IV) injection of a tracer, Image acquisition can begin nearly immediately after injection while the breast is gently immobilized (not painful: about 1 3 of the force used in mammography). Cancer cells avidly take up the tracer molecules and the emitted gamma rays are detected by a specialized gamma 6 SmartBreast offers two types of gamma camera systems for image acquisition: Eve Clear Scan™ model e680 has a single head array detector using the scintillator crystal sodium iodide (NaI). Eve Clear Scan™ model e750 has a dual head with direct conversion detectors using cadmium zinc telluride (CZT). The strikingly distinctive images produced by MBI provide clear visibility of the cancer in contrast to the generally unhelpful mammographic images in dense Example Case: woman with family history of breast cancer (mother) Mammography Eve Clear Scan™ Eve Clear Scan™ (COLORED) Right (CC) mammographic projection (far left) shows a heterogeneously dense breast that was interpreted as Right CC MBI image (middle) shows intense tracer uptake in cancer mass (arrow). All three (3) modalities have shown similar sensitivity to visualize the known cancers, but CESM and MBI have higher specifity (ability to predict malignancy) for additional cancers detected compared with 8 Furthermore, MBI is a better imaging method over MRI in the following situations: If you have any metal within your body, such as from a cochlear implant, clip in the brain, or cardiac implantable electronic devices (e.g., pacemaker, cardioverter defibrillator) If you have claustrophobia If you are overweight and find it difficult to lay on your stomach for up to an hour If you have severe allergies to medications or contrast agents If you have poor kidney function References 1 Shapiro S, Strax P, Venet “Periodic breast cancer screening in reducing mortality from breast cancer”. Our conversation about an elite’s habits hit My assistant coach said, “You have to change your body for your ” Anxiety crept Fleshman changed her body and lost her She wrote to us, readers, “injuries set ” They interrupted the first half of her professional running The night before this meet, I had eaten I had watched a movie with a teammate and went to bed around For the sake of balance, my night was intentional to feel Choices I made became challenged but I wanted to understand through his The coach’s view affects runners’ careers and relationships with their bodies and assistant coach’s shared perspective is an I committed to listen carefully to why he disagreed with her title and to keep an open Teammates in the van kept their ears His beliefs He was an assistant coach on Fleshman’s team before he came to About a month earlier, Mary Cain had brought abuse from Alberto Salazar into the spotlight . The former pro runner revealed her former coach’s notorious training As I sat in the passenger seat, I brought this instance to him and aimed to avoid a news recap everyone in the running world already She exposed Nike Oregon Project’s demands for her to lose weight in order to improve My assistant coach said, “Cain was not a good fit for the intensity Salazar ” I remembered, as a sixteen year old, I had stood in awe when Cain, then also sixteen years old, had earned two American high school At the same meet, I ran a PR I was proud of, a fairly impressive time for a high schooler, but she could have run laps around every athlete in my Cain proved breaking any record was I noticed my instinct to defend her to my assistant It is often taboo to talk about weight next to It is more accepted to associate wellbeing and performances from running, with coaches Those in authority have the chance to be honored with ethical conduct by athletes or even holiness, out of respect for the While all genders of coaches need to be trained on the problem of prioritizing weight before wellness, my assistant coach never recognized the gender bias in our He said, “your body naturally changes the harder you ” He ignored obvious and harmful patterns of behavior seen throughout the running community and focused on the literal fact that the cellular makeup of the body changes in response to exercise, without a mention that running on fumes alters the functioning of your I looked at the periphery of my younger self as we spoke, trying not to take what he said It felt like someone touched Initiatives Current Page: The Relationships Project Equity Scholar in Residence Model News & Blog Donate Now The Relationships Project Click here to participate The purpose of the Relationships Project is to uncover the wisdom found in relationships to help us in dismantling systemic racism and racial YouTube : The ILI Relationships Project The MRR Project Overview Description The goal of this project is to contribute to the work of dismantling systemic racism and racial Increasingly, social change agents understand that relationships are as critical to sustained and change as activism, politics and policy writer and activist adrienne maree brown has written that, in the work of social transformation, “relationships are ” The theory that drives our research is that strong multiracial relationships are an essential and powerful tool in the long work of dismantling The project assumes that biological race is a myth, unsupported by science and social history, created and maintained to support and enforce the subjugation of particular ethnic and cultural Racism, however, is alive and well, costing lives, degrading humanity, and limiting access to economic opportunity and basic human Many of us at the ILI are members of families, with parents, partners and or children whose skin color is different from each other’s and who don’t share the same experience of In order to be in loving family with each other, we see each other as fully human, transcending At the same time we acknowledge racism, and our differing realities, ancestral histories, and This project centers the stories of adult members of families, with parents, partners and or children whose skin color is different from each other’s and who don’t share the same experiences of racism and racial We are seeking participants to volunteer their perspectives for this project and hope to hear your Learning What We Know ILI senior research associates are conducting interviews with adult members of Participants will not be paid, or benefit financially from this Upon completing the interview process, transcripts of these conversations will be carefully read by a team to identify common themes, experiences and From those readings, the core team will generate Our timeline is to complete interviews by the end of May , analysis by , and to generate and begin implementing change strategies by September Impact We anticipate that the findings from our research will lend themselves to published materials, public webinars and events, and resources for organizations and community When our findings are established, we will develop a targeted strategy to drive change at those levels and through social Project Leadership This project is led by Karena Montag, MFT, Founding of STRONGHOLD and Lucinda Garthwaite, , Founding Director of the Institute for Liberatory Innovation .
